references: This work presents a federated Q-learning algorithm with pessimism for offline RL, which achieves linear speedup and low communication cost, while requiring only collaborative coverage of the optimal policy. Formally, we consider episodic finite-horizon tabular Markov decision processes (MDPs) with S𝑆S states, A𝐴A actions, and horizon length H𝐻H. A total number of M𝑀M agents, each with K𝐾K trajectories (collected using its local behavior policy), collaborate in a federated setting with the help of a central server to learn the optimal policy. Our main contributions are summarized as below; see also Table 1 for a detailed comparison.
